To find the maximum independent set in G, we can use a greedy algorithm. We will start with an empty set and iteratively add vertices to the set, ensuring that no two vertices in the set are adjacent.

1. Start with an empty set: {}
2. Add vertex 1: {1}
3. Skip vertex 2 (adjacent to 1)
4. Add vertex 3: {1, 3}
5. Skip vertex 4 (adjacent to 1 and 3)
6. Skip vertex 5 (adjacent to 3)
7. Add vertex 6: {1, 3, 6}
8. Skip vertex 7 (adjacent to 3 and 6)
9. Add vertex 8: {1, 3, 6, 8}
10. Skip vertex 9 (adjacent to 8)
11. Add vertex 10: {1, 3, 6, 8, 10}

The maximum independent set in G is {1, 3, 6, 8, 10}.
